  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Take your<strong> chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air then heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over medium-high heat</p><p>Pat the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> dry then coat them with the <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>ground coriander</strong>, a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> coated</strong> <strong>chicken</strong>, skin-side down and cook for 6 min or until the skins have slightly crisped</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1660751673721-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1660751673721-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1660751673721-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1660751673721-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1660751673721-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel the <strong>potatoes </strong>and<strong> </strong>cut<strong> </strong>into quarters</p><p>Chop the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to one side of a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1660751679050-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1660751679050-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1660751679050-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1660751679050-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1660751679050-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced leek</strong> to the middle of a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and<strong> </strong>a small knob of <strong>butter </strong>and mix everything together</p><p>Scrunch the edges of the foil around the leek to form a sealed parcel and add it to the baking tray</p><p>Once the chicken is slightly crispy, transfer it to the baking tray, reserve the pan and put the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> in the oven for 25-30 min or until the potatoes are golden and crisp and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1660751683554-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1660751683554-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
